cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a multi-tensor-based approach for learning from multi-view data, which involves multiple aspects and interactions among entities. This approach is suitable for large-scale problems and outperforms several state-of-the-art methods in terms of prediction accuracy and computational cost. Based on these characteristics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which focuses on the development and analysis of algorithms that improve their performance at some task with experience. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the representation, storage, organization, and access to information items; cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which studies the structure, dynamics, and function of social and information networks; cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which deals with the design, analysis, and implementation of efficient algorithms and data structures for solving computational problems; and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the development of intelligent agents that can perceive, reason, learn, and act in complex environments.
